<h2>The Agency-Specific Requirements</h2>
<p>Before comparing tools, it's worth being explicit about what agencies actually need that solo users don't:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Inbox isolation</strong> — a deliverability problem on Client A's campaign must not affect Client B's sending reputation</li>
  <li><strong>Sub-accounts or workspaces</strong> — each client should have their own environment with separate settings, sequences, and reporting</li>
  <li><strong>Master inbox</strong> — agency staff need to see all replies across all clients in one view without switching accounts</li>
  <li><strong>White-label reporting</strong> — clients want reports that look like they came from your agency, not from the tool vendor</li>
  <li><strong>Scalable pricing</strong> — per-seat pricing becomes expensive when you have 5 account managers handling 20 clients</li>
</ul>

